comment.narrative: 1) Complete eVIN preparatory assessment in Andaman & Nicobar Islands, Arunachal Pradesh, Delhi, Haryana, Jammu and Kashmir, Kerala, Ladakh, Lakshadweep, Meghalaya, Mizoram, Punjab, Sikkim, Tamil Nadu and West Bengal 2) Roll out the web based Vaccine Logistic and Cold Chain Management solution and train government staff in 9 States and 6 Union Territories covering 7500 cold chain points 3) Procure 6500 temperature loggers, 3400 phones and SIM cards for Cold Chain Handlers, Temperature Loggers

1) eVIN preparatory assessments completed in all states 2) Web based vaccine logistic and cold chain management solutions rolled out in 9 states and 6 Union Territories covering 7500 cold chain points 3) 3600 mobile phones, SIM cards for cold chain handlers and 6500 temperature loggers have been procured.

1. To undertake the baseline assessment of all districts of Andaman & Nicobar Islands, Chandigarh, Haryana, Kerala, Lakshadweep, Meghalaya, Mizoram, Puducherry, Punjab, Sikkim and Tamil Nadu with nearly 5500 cold chain points. 2. Roll out the web based Vaccine Logistic and Cold Chain Management solution and train government staff in above mentioned 11 states and UTs 3. Procure and install 10,000 temperature loggers 4. Updated training for the eVIN order management

1. Baseline assessment of all districts in Haryana, Kerala, Puducherry, Punjab and Tamil Nadu, with over 5500 cold chain points completed 2. The roll out of web based Vaccine Logistic and Cold Chain Management solution and training of government staff initiated un Haryana and Kerala. 3. 20,000 temperature loggers procured out of which 4000 temperature loggers installed and remaining are in the process of installation. 4. Updated training successfully completed.

1. Ensure the quality of vaccine supply chain data through the electronic vaccine intelligence network (eVIN) at nearly 17,000 public health facilities across the country. 2. Ensure the vaccine cold chain data through nearly 10,000 temperature loggers and install another 16,000 temperature loggers, through eVIN across the country.

1. Vaccine stocks are live on eVIN covering 11,181 CCPs across 374 districts of all 11 states. 2. 14,281 next-gen temperature loggers have been installed in 11 states and eVIN team continue to support in their monitoring.
